-- Azeri Oil Producer Hires Citigroup, Banks for $500 Million Bonds
-- B y   Z u l f u g a r   A g a y e v
-- 2012-01-30T11:38:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/azeri-oil-producer-hires-citigroup-banks-for-500-million-bonds.html
The State Oil Co. of Azerbaijan, or
Socar, hired Citigroup Inc.,  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK)  and the Royal Bank
of Scotland Plc to sell $500 million in Eurobonds.  Nomura International Plc and  Societe Generale (GLE)  SA will also
help manage the sale, the state-controlled Azeri energy producer
said today on its  website .  Socar, as the company is know, is in the final stages of
issuing the bonds, Socar President Rovnaq Abdullayev said Jan.
28 in an interview in Davos, Switzerland, where he was attending
the  World Economic Forum . He named Citigroup among the “major”
banks working on the sale.  “We will be active in the  capital markets ,” Abdullayev
said through a translator. Socar is planning new projects for
this year, he said, without elaborating.  Azerbaijan, on the Caspian Sea, is the third-biggest oil
producer in the former Soviet Union and companies led by London-
based  BP Plc (BP/)  have invested in the country’s oil and gas fields.
 Standard & Poor’s  upgraded Azerbaijan’s sovereign credit rating
one step to BBB-, the lowest investment grade, on Dec. 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
